# Adaptive Skill Loop (Permanent)

Clone of Hermes observe→distill→reuse→refine for Arch Systems. Canonical skill: `.cursor/skills/skill-self-improve/`.

## Always

1. **Progressive disclosure** — treat skill catalogs as Tier-1 (name+description); load full `SKILL.md` only when the task matches; load scripts/refs only when needed.
2. **Patch-first** — when improving a procedure, patch an existing skill before creating a new one.
3. **No policy fork** — never invent or soften `AGENTS.md`.

## After non-trivial work

1. Emit extended Alignment block (`02-agent-scoring.mdc`).
2. If Adaptive next is `distill` or `patch`, or criteria match (3+ similar successes, 5+ tool calls, error recovery, user correction, repeatable Alignment FAIL) → run **`skill-self-improve`**.
3. Validate with `pnpm ai check` when skills change.

## Token honesty

Report Tokens saved using the progressive-disclosure heuristic in `.cursor/skills/agent-alignment-score/references/extended-metrics.md`.

## Out of scope

- Vendoring Hermes runtime or DSPy+GEPA into this monorepo
- Auto-committing secrets into skills
